Class IntegerSchoolSearchTerm

    • cmc.controller.search.SchoolSearchTerm

  • public class IntegerSchoolSearchTerm

    • Method Detail

      • calculateMatch

        public double calculateMatch(java.lang.String comparison)
                      throws java.lang.NumberFormatException,
                             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Takes a String and scores it with a double from 0 to 1 based on how well it satisfies the term's requirements. For IntegerSchoolSearchTerm, the method will return 1 for any value within the term's range value, 0 for the furthest possible value from the range, and a linear gradient from 0 to 1 for intermediate values.
        Specified by:
        calculateMatch in class SchoolSearchTerm
        Parameters:
        comparison - the value to be compared as a String
        Returns:
        a score as a double from 0 to 1
        Throws:
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if the given String cannot be parsed by the method Integer.parseInt(String)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given String represents a number outside this term's restricted range

      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.String value)
              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Sets the value of the term using the String provided. The term's value type is based on the type of the subclass. Also sets included to true. For IntegerSchoolSearchTerm, the method takes a String value representing a single double or a range delineated by a colon (':'), e.g., "0:5", "15:16", "21:21", etc. A valid range from lower to upper must be true for (lower =< upper && lower >= this.min || upper =< this.max)
        Specified by:
        setValue in class SchoolSearchTerm
        Parameters:
        value - the value to be assigned to this term
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given String cannot be parsed to a valid integer range.
